  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top, tail, peel and finely dice the<strong> carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Wash the <strong>leek<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> thoroughly to remove any grit from between the leaves, then top, tail and slice finely</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/curried-haddock-leek-and-potato-chowder-df/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pot with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced carrot</strong> and <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>leek</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/curried-haddock-leek-and-potato-chowder-df/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a full kettle</p><p>Chop the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/curried-haddock-leek-and-potato-chowder-df/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve the <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 350ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/curried-haddock-leek-and-potato-chowder-df/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the leeks have softened, add the <strong>curry powder</strong>, <strong>ground turmeric</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>flour</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Add the<strong> vegetable stock, chopped potatoes </strong>and the<strong> single soya</strong> and cook for 15-18 min or until the potatoes are almost fork-tender</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/curried-haddock-leek-and-potato-chowder-df/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes<strong> </strong>are almost fork-tender, wash the <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with <strong>kitchen paper</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/curried-haddock-leek-and-potato-chowder-df/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>haddock bites </strong>and <strong>spinach</strong> to the potatoes and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Cook for 4-5 min or until the haddock is cooked through and the potatoes are fork-tender – this is your <strong>dairy-free</strong> <strong>curried haddock, leek & potato chowder</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/curried-haddock-leek-and-potato-chowder-df/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>dairy-free curried haddock, leek & potato chowder</strong> in bowls</p><p>Season with a generous grind of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
